eason.com/2019/03/19/the-supreme-courts-online-sales-tax-ruli/#comment-7720745">March.19.2019 at 10:15 am </a></div><div class="comment-content"><p>Lol at blaming scotus. This is a congressional issue.</p><p>The flat tax idea is a good one, but it cuts out the cities.</p><p>Perhaps the best solution is for the taxes to be payable based on the location of the business. Someone who drives across the city line to buy gas isn&#8217;t going to remit taxes back home.</p></div><div class="reply"></div></div><ol class="children"><li class="comment byuser even depth-2 parent " id="comment-7720773" data-sort-time="1553005418"><div id="div-comment-7720773" class="comment-body"><div class="comment-meta commentmetadata"><div class="comment-author vcard"> <cite class="fn"><strong>mpercy</strong></cite></div> <a href="https://reason.com/2019/03/19/the-supreme-courts-online-sales-tax-ruli/#comment-7720773">March.19.2019 at 10:23 am </a></div><div class="comment-content"><p>&#8220;Someone who drives across the city line to buy gas isn&#8217;t going to remit taxes back home.&#8221;</p><p>But they might owe them anyway, by law. It was the failure to get individuals who owed additional use taxes on out-of-state purchases that led states to try to force out-of-state vendors to be their proxy tax collectors.</p></div><div class="reply"></div></div><ol class="children"><li class="comment byuser odd alt depth-3" id="comment-7721638" data-sort-time="1553037716"><div id="div-comment-7721638" class="comment-body"><div class="comment-meta commentmetadata"><div class="comment-author vcard"> <cite class="fn"><strong>divigote</strong></cite></div> <a href="https://reason.com/2019/03/19/the-supreme-courts-online-sales-tax-ruli/#comment-7721638">March.19.2019 at 7:21 pm </a></div><div class="comment-content"><p><strong>Google is now paying $17000 to $22000 per month for working online from home. I have joined this job 2 months ago and i have earned $20544 in my first month from this job. I can say 