ncreased the local sales tax to reach the state maximum. Any tax software out of state vendors will purchase will not include any adjustment for all the rural areas of the US which are not subject to local sales taxes. Needless to say I have no vote in the town which collects local sales taxes from my purchases.</p><p>Just another unintended consequence of the SCOTUS decision. Not that I would expect Congress to do anything different wrt rural areas, but Congress had avoided the demands of states to address the issue for years and might still have failed to act, leaving things as they were.</p></div><div class="reply"></div></div></li><li class="comment byuser odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="comment-7727103" data-sort-time="1553327778"><div id="div-comment-7727103" class="comment-body"><div class="comment-meta commentmetadata"><div class="comment-author vcard"> <cite class="fn"><strong>dorseson</strong></cite></div> <a href="https://reason.com/2019/03/19/the-supreme-courts-online-sales-tax-ruli/#comment-7727103">March.23.2019 at 3:56 am </a></div><div class="comment-content"><p>Start working at home with Google! It&#8217;s by-far the best job I&#8217;ve had. Last Wednesday I got a brand new BMW since getting a check for $6474 this &#8211; 4 weeks past. I began this 8-months ago and immediately was bringing home at least $77 per hour. I work through this link, go to tech tab for work detail.<br /> >>>>>>>>>> <a href='http://www.GeoSalary.com'>http://www.GeoSalary.com</a></p></div><div class="reply"></div></div></li><li class="comment byuser even thread-even depth-1" id="comment-7727626" data-sort-time="1553382757"><div id="div-comment-7727626" class="comment-body"><div class="comment-meta commentmetadata"><div class="comment-author vcard"> <cite class="fn"><strong>Alan@.4</strong></cite></div> <a href="https://reason.com/2019/03/19/the-supreme-courts-online-sales-tax-ruli/#comment-7727626">March.23.2019 at 7:12 pm </a></div><div class="comment-content"><p>